  abstract = {The issue of class imbalance has become popular in the past 10 years as this term has been used frequently in Machine Learning. The biggest impact has been for the transfer learning approach to ML where the use of pre-trained models has raised the issue of bias stemming from using datasets with class imbalances. The study here, explore class imbalance impact on transfer learning models. This study also examines solutions to cater the problem of class imbalance by data augmentation, resampling methods, cost-sensitive learning, and synthetic data generation. This analysis examines 1119 academic papers from 2015 to 2025. Furthermore, this study inspects how alternate approaches for managing class imbalance affect model efficacy in diverse areas, including healthcare, anomaly detection, and sentiment analysis. The study depicts that more than 60% of transfer learning applications in imbalanced datasets are in domains such as healthcare and finance. Current trends like focal loss, adaptive re-weighting, generative adversarial networks for minority class augmentation, and self-supervised learning have become a hotspot area. The study's results highlight insightful future research areas to cater the issue of class imbalance and its major concerns in transfer learning domain.},
